text: Full Gear (2022) was a professional wrestling pay-per-view show made by All Elite Wrestling (AEW). It took place on November 19, 2022 at Prudential Center in Newark, New Jersey. It was the fourth Full Gear event made by AEW. The main event saw MJF defeat Jon Moxley to win the AEW World Championship. William Regal passed MJF a pair of brass knuckles when the referee was distracted. MJF then hit Moxley with them before getting the pinfall victory. On the show, Saraya made her return to in-ring action for the first time since since her career-ending injury in December 2017. ==Matches== No. Matches Stipulations Times 1 Best Friends (Chuck Taylor
